text:
Eh. Having tried once I won't return here. That about sums up my thoughts on this place.

It was off peak and I was the only customer. Yet the staff were more interested to chat among themselves and got my order wrong.

The rice is quite little. I have a regular male appetite and I had to get a bun afterwards in order to feel full.

Taste? Quite average. Price? Not so good compared to some of my regular places.
Big portion and good price. Tasty, not too salty, great varieties too! Love this stall to the max.

The price is affordable, the food looks good and feels also good.

It seems always crowded.

There were almost no available table when I was having my meal today, a lot of families having hotpot together. So I had to share a table with three other people.
the young gentleman who was serving me was very impatient, rude and stingy portions
